The mean (SD) age of the sample (n=2416) was 53 (10) years and 64.2% of them (n=1550) were males. Prevalence of suboptimal HDL was 17.6%. Regression analysis revealed female gender, (OR 7.73, 95% CI 5.99–9.97) younger age (OR 0.98, 95% CI 0.97–0.99), higher BMI (OR1.05. 95% CI 1.00–1.2) and LDL level over 100mg/dL (OR 1.004, 95% CI 1.00–1.007) had significant associations with suboptimal HDL.
