In a cross-sectional setting, 150 asymptomatic healthy premenopausal women without previously diagnosed hypertension, diabetes or known history cardiovascular diseases were consecutively enrolled. Ankle-brachial index (ABI), various parameters of general and central body fat distribution, and MetS were assessed.
